# City Page Template

Extracted from Valencia, Lisbon, and Chiang Mai — the three reference cities.
Every new city entry must follow this structure exactly.

> For the actionable pre-flight checklist and generation rules, see `new-city-generation.mdc`.
> For external link rules, see `external-links.mdc`.

---

## 1. Section order (matches page.tsx render order)

```
id, citySlug, countrySlug, city, country, tagline, summary, lastReviewed
→ actionChecklist
→ familyFit
→ weather       (always required — run scripts/generate_city_weather.py; adds sources.weather)
→ visa          (city-level object OR falls back to countries.json)
→ residency     (always required)
→ banking       (always required)
→ housing       (always required, full 4-block structure)
→ schools       (always required)
→ childcare     (always required, structured 3-block format)
→ healthcare    (always required, items array)
→ safety        (always required, items array)
→ cost          (always required, 3 fields)
→ sources
→ communityLinks
→ faq           (always required — 8 Q&As; see `new-city-generation.mdc` RULE 9)
```

**Note:** In `page.tsx`, FAQ renders between **Safety** and **Sources**; in JSON it lives **after** `communityLinks` (same pattern as Valencia). The **`weather`** block may appear anywhere in the JSON object; the page renders it after **Family fit** (see `app/[country]/[city]/page.tsx`).

### weather (climate normals)

- **Do not hand-write** monthly rows. After adding a new city to `data/cities.json` with `city`, `countrySlug`, and `id`, run:

  `python3 scripts/generate_city_weather.py`

  The script fills `weather` (NASA POWER / MERRA-2 monthly climatologies) and `sources.weather` (methodology links). For tiny places that fail geocoding, add coordinates to `MANUAL_COORDS` in the script.
- `weather.familyHighlights` is auto-generated for families (heat, cold, rain); review for city-specific tone if needed.

---

## 2. Required fields and content per section

### Top-level metadata
```json
{
  "id": "cityname-countrycode",
  "citySlug": "city-name",
  "countrySlug": "country-name",
  "city": "City Name",
  "country": "Country Name",
  "tagline": "One-line hook — specific, benefit-first, honest",
  "summary": "2–4 sentences. What makes this city good for families. Main trade-off last.",
  "lastReviewed": "YYYY-MM"
}
```

### actionChecklist
- 8–10 items
- Every item must have `targetSection` pointing to one of: `visa`, `housing`, `schools`, `healthcare`, `childcare`, `residency`, `banking`
- At most 1–2 items can be general advice without a target (e.g. timing/logistics)
- Labels: imperative verb first, city-specific detail, em-dash for the key reason
- Cover: visa path → housing → schools → healthcare → residency → banking → 90-day/admin

```json
{ "label": "Apply for the DTV at a Thai embassy — bring income proof and $15,000 in savings", "targetSection": "visa" }
```

### familyFit
- `bestFor`: 4 items — specific family archetypes, not generic praise
- `watchOutFor`: 4 items — honest, specific trade-offs, not disclaimers
- Never use "it depends" or vague warnings

### visa
City-level `visa` object (required unless country already in `data/countries.json`).
Each option must have:
- `type`, `duration`, `description`
- `anchor` (e.g. `"visa-eu"`, `"visa-dtv"`) — enables VisaPathSelector interactivity
- `detailTitle` and `details[]` — flat bullet list of actionable steps
- `officialLink` where a stable official URL exists

Anchor → path mapping (must register in VisaPathSelector.tsx if new):
- `visa-eu` → `"eu"`
- `visa-tourist` → `"tourist"`
- `visa-dtv`, `visa-d8`, `visa-dnv`, `visa-elite` → `"dnv"`

Tip: 1 sentence, practical (e.g. "Book your consulate appointment early — slots fill in major cities").

### residency
Always required. Use local terminology explained in plain words.
```json
{
  "title": "Registration & [local name]",
  "tip": "One actionable sentence with a URL if possible.",
  "items": [
    "What the system is (or isn't) — in plain words",
    "What you must do first, when, and why it matters",
    "The document/step that unlocks everything else",
    "Periodic reporting or renewal if applicable",
    "What serves as your ID for daily admin"
  ]
}
```

### banking
Always required.
```json
{
  "title": "Banking",
  "tip": "The one thing that blocks account opening — state it upfront.",
  "items": [
    "Which banks expats actually use and why",
    "Exact documents needed to open an account",
    "Digital/neobank bridge option while waiting",
    "International transfer method (Wise/Revolut)",
    "Cash culture note — how much to keep on hand"
  ]
}
```

### housing
Full 4-block structure. No housing section without all four.
```json
{
  "summary": "1–2 sentences: price context + top family area.",
  "bestAreas": ["Area1", "Area2", "Area3", "Area4", "Area5"],
  "searchPortalsIntro": [
    "These are local rental platforms — this is where residents rent long-term housing (cheaper than Airbnb).",
    "Search '[City Name]' inside each platform to filter local listings.",
    "Tip: [city-specific short-stay arrival advice]."
  ],
  "searchPortals": [
    { "label": "PortalName — brief description", "url": "https://rooturl.com" },
    { "label": "Search on Facebook: '[Group Name]' — brief description" }
  ],
  "typicalPrices": [
    "1-bed flat, [area]: [local currency range]/month",
    "3-bed house/flat, [area]: [local currency range]/month",
    "3-bed [premium area]: [local currency range]/month",
    "Short-stay serviced option: [local currency range]/month"
  ],
  "whatYouNeedToRent": [
    "Passport",
    "[Local ID or tax number if required]",
    "[Bank statements / income proof]",
    "[Deposit terms — local norm]",
    "[Contract note — any local quirks]"
  ]
}
```

**Housing link rules** (see external-links.mdc):
- Portal URLs: root homepage only, never filtered search results
- Facebook: plain text label only, no URL

### schools
```json
{
  "summary": "1–2 sentences: quality context + key practical warning.",
  "publicSystem": "Honest 2–3 sentence assessment. Is it viable for expat children? If not, say so clearly.",
  "internationalOptions": "Where the schools are located, curricula available, rough fee range, application lead time.",
  "languageNotes": "Language of instruction. English availability. What happens if child attends local school.",
  "tip": "One urgent, specific action (e.g. 'Apply to X before booking flights — waitlists stretch 12 months').",
  "examples": [
    { "name": "School Name", "curriculum": "IB / British / US", "fees": "$X,000 – $Y,000 / yr", "url": "https://schoolwebsite.com" }
  ]
}
```
- 3 example schools minimum, each with a real URL
- Fees as approximate ranges, not precise figures
- Remove URL if only a social media page exists

### childcare
Three structured blocks — no paragraph format.
```json
{
  "summary": "1–2 sentences: overall availability and standout fact.",
  "daycareItems": [
    "What nurseries are called locally, age they accept, where they cluster",
    "Typical price range (local currency)",
    "State/subsidised option and whether it's realistic",
    "Visit-in-person advice"
  ],
  "nannyItems": [
    "Full-time rate (local currency / month)",
    "Part-time rate (local currency / hr)",
    "Cultural note (experience with expat families, language, etc.)",
    "Timing tip (how early to start searching)"
  ],
  "whereToFindItems": [
    "Platform or Facebook group name — why it works here",
    "Secondary platform",
    "Community word-of-mouth note"
  ]
}
```

### healthcare
Items array required. No summary-only entries.
```json
{
  "tip": "The single most important action (e.g. 'Register at your clinic in the first week').",
  "summary": "1–2 sentences: public vs private split, overall quality.",
  "items": [
    "Public system access (or lack of it) — what expats actually use",
    "Name the top 1–2 hospitals/clinics and what makes them the right choice",
    "Cost anchor: GP = X, specialist = Y, emergency = Z",
    "Insurance: what type, which providers, price range for family",
    "Any practical detail unique to this city (medevac, pharmacy, language)"
  ]
}
```

### safety
Items array required. No summary-only entries.
```json
{
  "score": 75,
  "summary": "1 sentence: general verdict.",
  "items": [
    "Violent crime assessment — honest, not just reassuring",
    "The real #1 daily risk (road, weather, petty theft, etc.)",
    "City/island-specific hazard if one exists (smoke season, jellyfish, heat)",
    "Area contrast (safe neighbourhoods vs areas to avoid)",
    "Any legal/social norm that affects family behaviour"
  ]
}
```

### cost
Exactly 3 fields, single approximate values in local currency.
```json
{
  "status": "estimated",
  "rentRange": "~€1,300 / month",
  "familyDinner": "~€45",
  "nannyRate": "~€12 / hr"
}
```

### sources
Only official, institutional, or stable public URLs.
- `visa[]`, `schools[]`, `housing[]` (optional), `healthcare[]` (optional), `cost[]`
- Community links (Facebook groups) go in `communityLinks`, not `sources`

