## 3. Writing style rules

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|---|---|---|
| Verbs first | "Register at your Junta de Freguesia within 90 days" | "The Junta de Freguesia is where you register" |
| Explain local terms inline | "Padrón Municipal — Spain's official address register" | "Register on the Padrón" |
| Answer what / when / why | "Get your NIF at any Finanças office (the tax office) — needed for every transaction" | "You need a NIF" |
| 1–2 lines per bullet | Keep bullets to 1 sentence with one em-dash clause | 3-line bullets |
| Hedges where appropriate | "typically", "usually", "many families", "roughly" | "always", "guaranteed", "the best" |
| Local currency | "~฿9,000 / month" | "$265/month" |
| Named specifics | "Bangkok Bank and Kasikorn (KBank)" | "local banks" |

---

## 4. What NOT to include

- **Superlatives without evidence**: "the safest city in the world", "virtually zero crime", "world-class"
- **Precise unverifiable numbers**: exact government fee amounts, exact visa processing times in days
- **Deep search URLs**: filtered/search-result portal URLs (root homepage only)
- **Facebook URLs for schools or unstable institutions**: use plain text if only a social page exists
- **Border run encouragement**: do not suggest visa runs as a strategy
- **USD-only costs for non-USD cities**: use local currency; USD is acceptable as secondary context only
- **Cleveland Clinic in Dubai**: it's in Abu Dhabi, not Dubai
- **Score inflation**: safety scores should reflect honest risk, not marketing. Cities with road/medevac risks should be 78–85, not 90+

---

## 5. Checklist structure rules

- Every important item must have `targetSection`
- `targetSection` must match one of: `"visa"`, `"housing"`, `"schools"`, `"childcare"`, `"healthcare"`, `"residency"`, `"banking"`, `"safety"`
- General logistics items (timing, SIM card, equipment) may omit `targetSection` — max 2 per checklist
- Order: visa → housing → schools → healthcare → residency → banking → practical/logistics
- Label format: `"[Verb] [what] — [why it matters or when]"`

---

## 6. Data rules

- `rentRange`: single approximate value in local currency with `~` prefix — NOT a range
- `familyDinner`: single approximate value — a mid-range restaurant meal for 2 adults + 1–2 kids
- `nannyRate`: single approximate hourly rate — NOT monthly, NOT daycare
- Safety score: use 75–90 range for realistic cities; never above 92
- All figures marked `"status": "estimated"` unless sourced from an official document
- Housing `typicalPrices` may use ranges (they are detail bullets, not card metrics)
